  "prompt": "What is a zero sum game?",
  "response": "A zero-sum game is a concept in game theory where the total gain and loss of all participants add up to zero. In other words, one person's gain is exactly balanced by another person's loss. Some key characteristics include:\n\n1. Total resources are fixed\n2. Gain for one player means an equivalent loss for another\n3. The total value of gains and losses always equals zero\n\nExamples of zero-sum games include:\n- Poker\n- Chess\n- Gambling\n- Some economic trading scenarios\n\nIn contrast, non-zero-sum games allow for situations where all participants can gain or lose together.",
